%TUTORIAL -`-`- ZIL - MEMBER SELECTION LIST -`-`- TUTORIAL
%SELECTION ===>_ZCMD
+

 If the@OPTION+field is left blank, a member selection list is displayed for
 the specified source library name.  You may select members for compilation or
 editing by entering the appropriate code in the selection field:

  !F$to compile a function
  !M$to compile a module
  !P$to compile a program
  !E$to edit the source member
+
 You may specify a different name for the resulting load module by
 entering the alternate name in the "LOADMOD" field next to the member name.
 Any value that was present in the@OVERRIDING NAME+field on the XZIL option 4
 panel is ignored when the member list is used.

